        "kearny": "Kearny, located in Hudson County and bordered by Essex County, has its residential foreclosure proceedings handled through the Hudson County Superior Court's Chancery Division in Jersey City. Kearny's working-class neighborhoods and mix of older single-family and multi-family homes have historically seen elevated foreclosure activity during economic downturns, and the court's caseload from the broader Hudson County area can mean meaningful delays between filing and final judgment.",
        "west-new-york": "West New York, a Hudson County town sitting directly across the Hudson River from Midtown Manhattan, has its foreclosure cases processed through the Hudson County Superior Court in Jersey City. Despite its small geographic footprint, West New York's high-density residential buildings mean that when foreclosure filings do arise, they often involve condominiums or co-ops where title and lien structures require careful attention before any sale decision is made.",
        "new-brunswick": "New Brunswick, the seat of Middlesex County, has its foreclosure proceedings run through the Middlesex County Superior Court — Chancery Division — located right in the city. Middlesex County maintains an active foreclosure docket, and New Brunswick's dense urban core combined with Rutgers University's surrounding residential neighborhoods means the court regularly processes a wide range of residential mortgage foreclosure matters under New Jersey's Fair Foreclosure Act.",
        "edison": "Edison Township, one of Middlesex County's largest municipalities, sees all of its foreclosure cases filed with the Middlesex County Superior Court — Chancery Division — in New Brunswick. Edison's vast suburban landscape and high volume of single-family homes mean the Middlesex County Chancery Division handles a consistent stream of residential foreclosure filings, and the statewide timeline from Notice of Intent to sheriff's sale can run anywhere from 18 months to over three years depending on whether the homeowner contests the action."
