        "fort-lee": "Fort Lee is part of Bergen County, and any inherited property there must go through the Bergen County Surrogate's Court in Hackensack before title can be transferred to a new owner. Fort Lee's dense condominium market means many inherited units also require coordination with condo associations in addition to the probate process, adding a layer of logistics that cash buyers are well-equipped to navigate.",
        "paramus": "Paramus real estate passes through the Bergen County Surrogate's Court in Hackensack when it's part of a decedent's estate, and the standard probate timeline in Bergen County — from filing to receiving usable letters testamentary — often runs six to ten weeks under normal conditions. Heirs in Paramus dealing with a family home or commercial-adjacent residential property benefit from knowing that New Jersey's inheritance tax lien attaches at death, meaning that lien must be resolved before or at closing regardless of sale price.",
        "teaneck": "Teaneck properties in Bergen County go through the Bergen County Surrogate's Court in Hackensack for probate administration, and with Teaneck's notably diverse and multigenerational homeownership patterns, inherited estates here sometimes involve multiple heirs who must all agree before a sale can proceed. Getting all beneficiaries aligned early — alongside the formal Surrogate's process — is key to moving an inherited Teaneck home toward a clean closing.",
