        "bergenfield": "Bergenfield is a Bergen County borough whose inherited real estate matters are handled by the Bergen County Surrogate's Court in Hackensack, typically requiring several months from the date of death to reach a point where the estate can convey clear title. If the decedent owned the home solely in their name without survivorship rights, a full probate proceeding — not just an affidavit — will be required before a buyer can get title insurance and close.",
        "jersey-city": "Jersey City is Hudson County's largest city, and the Hudson County Surrogate's Court on Newark Avenue in Jersey City itself handles probate for estates that include Jersey City real property — a convenience for local heirs compared to some counties where the courthouse is farther away. Given Jersey City's rapid appreciation in property values over recent years, inherited homes here often carry significant equity, and clearing the estate process efficiently can make a meaningful financial difference for beneficiaries ready to sell.",
